CatDescriptText: Mrs. Annie Cabbell, 2901 Wylie Avenue, was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 25, 1958, pg. A1 with question: "Do you think that business and employment are as good as the Eisenhower administration declares that it is?" answer reads: "No, I don't. And the reason is that there are too many people out of work."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Annie Cabbell wearing tweed suit, light colored blouse with bow at collar, and eyeglasses, standing on sidewalk with trees and automobiles in background
